, because she had been persuaded by that.  For us, French people, it looked very true, they were living in the same ways, and very conformist ideas \endash  they hated people with the beard, for in
stance, because it was Castro.  They thought they had the best political system in the world, that everybody should follow their model, and it was a one-dimensional thinking like Marcuse put it.  That was before the start of the free speech movement. But 
that was as far as I went in terms of dealing with political or cultural ideas.
